## Why this matters

Depending on the service, exposure of this kind can lead to:

- Unauthorised access to data or controls
- Inclusion in opportunistic credential-stuffing or scanning campaigns
- Use as a pivot into your internal network
- Regulatory exposure under the Data Privacy Act of 2012 if personal data is involved

## What I am asking

Please consider one or more of the following:

1. Place the service behind a VPN or zero-trust access proxy
2. Restrict the source IP range that can reach the service to known administrative ranges
3. Apply the latest vendor firmware or software update
4. If the service is no longer needed, decommission it

